Title: Pages Currently Active 
Link: https://platform.stratascratch.com/coding/10556-pages-currently-active?code_type=3
Level: Medium

You are monitoring a system where pages can be turned on or off at different times.
The page status log records every state change event for each page.
Find the number of pages that are currently active based on their most recent status change.
Return the count of currently active pages.

Data page_status_log:
changed_at: datetime
event_id: bigint
page_id: bigint
status: text

>.<

Solution:

select count(*) as active_pages
from page_status_log p
join (
select page_id,max(changed_at) as last_changed
from page_status_log
group by page_id
) last_event
on p.page_id = last_event.page_id and p.changed_at = last_event.last_changed
where p.status = 'on';

Output:

active_pages
2
